What are Multifocal Contact Lenses?
Multifocal contact lenses are specialized vision correction devices designed to address presbyopia by providing multiple focal points for near, intermediate, and distance vision within a single lens. Unlike traditional bifocals, these advanced optical solutions utilize innovative designs like concentric rings or gradual power transitions to enable seamless visual clarity across varying distances.
These lenses eliminate the need for separate reading glasses while offering superior comfort and optical performance compared to older vision correction methods. Modern multifocal designs incorporate cutting-edge materials like silicone hydrogels that enhance oxygen permeability and moisture retention for all-day comfort.
